  • Field Details

    • m_trigger

      ByteBuffer m_trigger
      When non-null, holds a ByteBuffer that windows the structurs at *td_trigger.

      In a bit of an incestuous relationship, this will be set by the trigger() method below, which returns the corresponding instance of LookupImpl.CallImpl.TriggerDataImpl. That class has a package-visible withTriggerData method that the caller can use to run client code in a scope throughout which that Trigger instance will be associated with this instance and can read from this ByteBuffer.

      On exit of that scope, this field will be reset to null and the association between the TriggerImpl instance and this broken.

      The dispatcher will execute client specialize and apply methods within such a scope, so those methods will see a Trigger instance that works, while avoiding thorny questions here about cache validity, since every call will use the structure freshly passed by PostgreSQL.
